  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1294\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2023-01-19 at 18 12 11\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/213427846-4ed4bbcc-66fb-4316-a1f6-4eba1f778cc7.png\">\r\n\r\nthis only happens since v1.3.0\r\n\r\nthe log:\r\n```\r\nJan-19 10:43:38.374[]                ^[[34mdebug^[[39m: Request error, retrying routeId=submitPoolAttestations, baseUrl=http://65.109.31.200:9596 Internal Server Error: Multiple errors on submitPoolAttestations\r\nPublishError.InsufficientPeers\r\nPublishError.InsufficientPeers\r\nError: Internal Server Error: Multiple errors on submitPoolAttestations\r\nPublishError.InsufficientPeers\r\nPublishError.InsufficientPeers\r\n    at HttpClient.requestWithBody (file:///usr/app/packages/api/src/utils/client/httpClient.ts:258:15)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:95:5)\r\n```\r\n\r\nNot sure if it happens with v1.4.0 since it mostly happens on mainnet nodes\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\n\r\n- No error",
